WEBVTT

00:00.580 --> 00:03.330
Ciao Lain, sei stata bene?

00:03.560 --> 00:05.380
Sì, e tu?

00:05.560 --> 00:09.640
Yes, I’ve been fine. I’m a bit tired, though.

00:10.160 --> 00:11.300
Stanco?

00:11.300 --> 00:15.000
Sì, sono stato abbastanza impegnato.

00:15.370 --> 00:16.330
Quanto?

00:16.620 --> 00:24.330
Ehm, beh... Almeno parlarti così è qualcosa che mi piace.

00:24.810 --> 00:25.520
Davvero?

00:25.520 --> 00:31.180
Really! What shall we talk about today... What do you want to talk about, Lain?

00:32.180 --> 00:36.160
Non potevamo parlare molto di te lo scorso mese.

00:37.010 --> 00:42.860
I’d rather talk about you, though, Lain; not about myself.

00:44.170 --> 00:51.960
But you’re right, it’s only fair that we both get to talk about what we want, so this time we’ll talk about me. But next time we’ll talk about you, Lain. Is that all right?

00:52.290 --> 00:52.920
Okay!

00:53.900 --> 01:08.520
I’m not sure where I should start, though... My name is Younera Touko, I’m 27, I’m a doctor at the Tokyo Research Institute for Psychotherapy... That's all about me.

01:09.930 --> 01:12.980
Ah, non andremo da nessuna parte così.

01:14.020 --> 01:20.800
You know, I’m used to listening people talk, not talking myself.

01:21.620 --> 01:24.170
Is there anything you’d like to know, Lain?

01:24.640 --> 01:26.410
Come sei diventato un dottore?

01:26.660 --> 01:30.640
Ho studiato molto in un posto chiamato università.

01:30.640 --> 01:37.140
Ho scritto una cosa chiamata tesi e con quella ho ricevuto la mia laurea per diventare un dottore.
